00:28:05.590 --> 00:28:06.590
government.

00:28:06.590 --> 00:28:12.809
And so, they publish these results online.

00:28:12.809 --> 00:28:18.820
And so, because it's coming from an objective
source, I'm more inclined to believe that

00:28:18.820 --> 00:28:21.460
and that they can't be manufactured that way.

00:28:21.460 --> 00:28:28.429
&gt;&gt;male #3: So you make the case that the top
leadership is more meritocratic because--

00:28:28.429 --> 00:28:29.429
&gt;&gt;Ann Lee: I'm sorry, what?

00:28:29.429 --> 00:28:30.549
&gt;&gt; male #3: Is more meritocratic, meritocratic
because--

00:28:30.549 --> 00:28:31.549
&gt;&gt;Ann Lee: Meritocratic.

00:28:31.549 --> 00:28:32.549
&gt;&gt; male #3: Because--

00:28:32.549 --> 00:28:33.830
&gt;&gt;Ann Lee: The US or the--?

00:28:33.830 --> 00:28:34.830
I'm sorry.

00:28:34.830 --> 00:28:35.830
Can you--?

00:28:35.830 --> 00:28:36.830
&gt;&gt; male #3: The top.

00:28:36.830 --> 00:28:37.830
&gt;&gt;Ann Lee: The top.

00:28:37.830 --> 00:28:39.509
&gt;&gt; male #3: You make the case that the top
leadership in China is more meritocratic because

00:28:39.509 --> 00:28:43.340
they aren't driven by electoral politics,
[inaudible]-ism, and so on.

00:28:43.340 --> 00:28:51.000
So do you see that people in remote areas
of China, if they have the merit, like Tibet

00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:56.490
or other regions, can make it to the top leadership
of China in Communist Party?

00:28:56.490 --> 00:29:00.980
&gt;&gt;Ann Lee: So the question is do the other
people believe they can make it to the top

00:29:00.980 --> 00:29:01.980
if they--?

00:29:01.980 --> 00:29:02.980
&gt;&gt; male #3: Yeah.

00:29:02.980 --> 00:29:03.980
Do people believe in--?

00:29:03.980 --> 00:29:04.980
&gt;&gt;Ann Lee: Yeah, yeah.

00:29:04.980 --> 00:29:07.720
And Hu Jintao and Wen Xiaobao are exactly
two examples.

00:29:07.720 --> 00:29:11.700
Both of them did not come from privilege at
all.

00:29:11.700 --> 00:29:18.240
They didn't have Revolutionary background
from their parents or anybody else.

00:29:18.240 --> 00:29:22.549
They came from the poor, rural areas of China.

00:29:22.549 --> 00:29:29.830
And because they were able to prove themselves
over time, pass the testing, get involved

00:29:29.830 --> 00:29:33.460
and prove themselves through merit, they got
to the top.

00:29:33.460 --> 00:29:39.160
And therefore, in some ways it's almost more
democratic because it doesn't rely on you

00:29:39.160 --> 00:29:45.650
being able to be a billionaire to run for
office, or that you sell your soul to a corporation.

00:29:45.650 --> 00:29:51.240
It's about you making it to the top on your
merits of your own performance.

00:29:51.240 --> 00:29:54.220
&gt;&gt; male #4: Hi.

00:29:54.220 --> 00:29:59.970
I wonder if you could explain for me what
